We seek a switched-on Project Installation Manager to install coding equipment
in manufacturing environments and ensure the highest completion standards.

** About the role **

If you are a Project Installation Manager seeking a company in the growth
phase, have a continuous improvement mindset, and are looking for an
organisation where you can see the direct impact of the value you are adding
to the customer and team and want to be part of a team that welcomes new
joiners and fresh input, this could be the next career move for you. The role
is based in Wakerley, Brisbane and reports directly to the National Project
Manager.

As a PIM, you will be responsible for:

  * working with the sales team to scope projects, 
  * assisting customers with software-related fault finding and 
  * Installing equipment of all scales/ sizes. 
  * Accounting for every detail, 
  * Meticulous in their planning 
  * Paying great attention to detail. 
  * They will also think outside the box to solve technical issues, 

This is an autonomous role with your territory, but whilst you’ll frequently
visit customers on the road, there will also be occasional interstate travel.
However, we are a company that believes we are stronger together. Therefore,
you will work closely with the sales team, installation team, automation
engineers, and project coordinators and feel very much at the heart of
everything happening.

** About you **

This is an excellent opportunity for many candidates looking for a fresh
challenge, as the ideal candidate could come from various backgrounds.

  * Have an electrical or mechanical trade qualification. 
  * A High technical aptitude for electro/mechanical systems and software. 
  * Well-developed technical skill set, with some exposure to PLC or system integration 
  * The successful candidate will have excellent attention to detail and be experienced in hardware installation and commissioning. 
  * We also seek a candidate with a continuous improvement mindset and looking to join an organisation for the long term and build their career. 

** Benefits **

  * The great benefit of joining Insignia is that you will be fully trained on our in-house/ Domino equipment. 
  * 2023 Certified A Great Place to Work! 
  * Free On-site Parking 
  * Birthday leave- be paid to have your birthday off, doing what you love. 
  * Access to a free Onsite physio 
  * Access to counselling, financial coaching, nutritional support, and legal consultation to assist you and your family through our Employee Assistance Program 
  * Social club, monthly BBQs, morning teas, and Christmas parties 
  * Employee of the Month awards and Safety awards 
  * Training and development opportunities 
  * Study Leave for an approved qualification. 

** Insignia ** is a leading national distributor of industrial labelling and coding equipment and a label producer with over 50 years of experience in the Australian packaging market. We have multiple production and warehousing facilities nationwide, supported by national sales and technical service offices. We are renowned for quality, innovation, progressive customer solutions and relationship management. We have a strong history of success and are growth-focused for the future, and we value and respect individuals within our business. 

What makes working at ** Insignia ** special? First, we are passionate about
our vision of Helping Australia Compete—and we’ve been successfully doing so
for over 50 years.

** Applications: **

If you are excited by our culture and motivated to contribute to Winson
Group’s success, we want to hear from you!

** All applicants must have unlimited working rights in Australia. **

